<TITLE> DSE opens new office in Chittagong </TITLE>
<TEXT>
 CHITTAGONG, Nov 22 (bdnews24.com) -- The Dhaka Stock Exchange opened its new office in Chittagong Thursday as part of an ongoing policy to increase capital market investment opportunities around the country. The chairman of the Securities and Exchange Commission, Faruq Ahmad Siddiqi, inaugurated DSE's new office at Shafi Bhaban in the city's Agrabad Commercial Area. DSE representatives said the new office was part of their plan to create secondary markets in divisional headquarters using state-of-the-art automated transaction systems. Modern automated transaction systems will enable brokers to connect with the DSE's branch offices and take part in trading, the DSE officials said. So far, 17 DSE members have started brokerage operations in the Chittagong office, which will provide investors with all facilities, including fast-cash deposits and withdrawals through online banking. Speakers at the inauguration ceremony said the role of the capital market in a country's economic development is indispensable. Also present at the event were DSE president Abdullah Bokhari, Chittagong Chamber of Commerce president Saifuzzaman Chowdhury and DSE's chief executive Salahuddin Ahmed Khan. bdnews24.c
